"title": "8846: ungodliness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8846",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The state of believing in God, while adopting a lifestyle which seems to deny this. Believers are warned to guard against ungodliness.</p>\n<h2>Expressions of ungodliness</h2>\n<h3>A defiant spirit towards God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:6\">MAT 7:6</a></strong> <em>Jesus Christ is teaching his disciples not to share the riches of spiritual truth with persons who are persistently unappreciative, vicious and defiant.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job36:8-Job36:13\">JOB 36:8–36:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:8-Ps73:11\">PSA 73:8–73:11</a></p>\n<h3>Mocking God and/or his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:3-2Pet3:4\">2PE 3:3–3:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:15-Ps35:16\">PSA 35:15–35:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:40-Acts13:41\">ACT 13:40–13:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab1:5\">HAB 1:5</a></p>\n<h3>Evil behaviour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa32:6-Isa32:7\">ISA 32:6–32:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:9\">PRO 11:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah1:1-Jonah1:2\">JON 1:1–1:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:9-1Tim1:11\">1TI 1:9–1:11</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of ungodliness</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:15-2Chr36:16\">2CH 36:15–36:16</a> <em>the southern kingdom of Judah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps52:1-Ps52:3\">PSA 52:1–52:3</a> <em>Doeg the Edomite</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:13-Isa9:17\">ISA 9:13–9:17</a> <em>the northern kingdom of Israel</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:11-Jer23:12\">JER 23:11–23:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:15-Jer23:17\">JER 23:15–23:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:9-1Cor6:11\">1CO 6:9–6:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:1-Eph2:3\">EPH 2:1–2:3</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:1-2Tim3:5\">2TI 3:1–3:5</a> <em>people in general during the last days (the time between the first and second comings of Jesus Christ)</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:16\">HEB 12:16</a> <em>Esau</em></p>\n<h2>God will judge the ungodly</h2>\n<h3>In this life</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:31\">PRO 11:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:28-Prov1:33\">PRO 1:28–1:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:33-Prov3:34\">PRO 3:33–3:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa10:5-Isa10:7\">ISA 10:5–10:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa33:14\">ISA 33:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:18\">ROM 1:18</a></p>\n<h3>At the final judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:7\">2PE 3:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job27:8\">JOB 27:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:34\">PRO 3:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:18\">1PE 4:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:4-2Pet2:10\">2PE 2:4–2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:14-Jude1:15\">JUD 1:14–1:15</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ died for the ungodly</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:6-Rom5:8\">ROM 5:6–5:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:26\">ROM 11:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:20\">ISA 59:20</a></p>\n<h2>God's people must guard against ungodliness</h2>\n<h3>By relying upon God's grace</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:11-Titus2:12\">TIT 2:11–2:12</a></strong></p>\n<h3>By putting no confidence in ungodly people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:1\">1CO 6:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps1:1\">PSA 1:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:3-Jude1:4\">JUD 1:3–1:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:17-Jude1:19\">JUD 1:17–1:19</a></p>\n<h3>By avoiding ungodly teaching and behaviour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:16\">2TI 2:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:7\">1TI 4:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:20-1Tim6:21\">1TI 6:20–6:21</a></p>",
